Name: poly(ethylene oxide)
Reference: Kim, Il Tae; Lee, Ji Hoon; Shofner, Meisha L.; Jacob, Karl; Tannenbaum, Rina , Polymer , 53 , 12 , 2402-2411 (2012)
Remarks: [PEO] purchased from Aldrich, MW=300000 (reported), [m-CNT] oxidized MWCNT/Fe(NO3)3 (4/1wt), NaDDBS and propylene oxide mixed for 30min, the mixt. dried for 3days at 100C, the powder products washed with water and EtOH several times and dried at 50C, then the powder calcined at 500C for 2h under Ar, gamma-Fe2O3 nanoparticles tethered onto the surface of CNT (SEM), [MWCNT] purity>99%, d=ca.20nm, l=10micron, [NaDDBS] sodium dodecylbenzene sulfonate
Mixing / Blending method: PEO/water soln. and m-CNT/EtOH dispersion mixed at 50C for 12h and degassed under vacuum
State after processing: Crystal73.5[%](DSC,Heating rate=10C/min, second heating,Taking melting enthalpy of 100% cryst. PEO 205J/g)
[proc] Solvent casting: The mixt. soln. cast into glass mold and to align m-CNT low magnetic field (<0.3T) applied to the soln. at 50C for 1h, then dried overnight at 50C
[elecon] remarks: Value parallel to the externally-applied magnetic field (aligned direction)

Name: polyaniline
[proc] Compression: compression molded at 120C and 20MPa for 10min in vacuum
Reference: Yan, Haiyan; Kou, Kaichang , Journal of Materials Science , 49 , 3 , 1222-1228 (2014)
Remarks: [multi-walled carbon nanotube(MWCNT)]purity>95%, average diameter 25nm and length between 5 and 10micron, purchased from Shenzhen Nanotech Port Co. Ltd.(China), [pretreatment of CNT]CNT dispersed in sodium dodecyl sulfate(SDS) and ultrasonicated for 4h, separated by centrifugation, washed with acetone and dried, [PANI-coated CNT(PANI-CNT)]aniline polymerized in HCl solution(pH=2) at RT for 12h using ammonium persulfate as oxidizing agent in the presence of pretreated CNT
Mixing / Blending method: PANI-CNT and PANI powders mixed by ultrasonication in ethanol for 1h, then milled at 600rpm for 2h using a planetary ball mill, then the mixed powders dried at 60C for 6h in vacuum
[poly] Post-treatment: PANI ground to fine powders smaller than 50micron by using an agate mortar and a pestle
Morphology: CNT homogeneously dispersed in the polymer matrix

Name: poly(prop-1-ene)
[proc] Compression: First pressed at RT for 5min (ram d=42.7mm), then pressed at 120C, 70MPa and baked at 150C, 35MPa for 15min
Reference: Panwar, Varij; Park, Jong-Oh; Park, Suk-Ho; Kumar, Sanjeev; Mehra, RM , Journal of Applied Polymer Science , 115 , 3 , 1306-1314 (2010)
Remarks: [PP] H200 MA, manufd. by Indian Petrochemicals Corp. granule, white, semiopaque, d.=0.95g/cm3, hardness (shore D)=ca. 68-83, melt flow=0.5-136g/10min, Tm=165C, MW=5.046E(4), dielectric constant at 1MHz=2.2-2.6, dissipation factor at 1MHz=0.0003-0.0005, vol. resistivity=1E(13) ohm*cm, [graphite] av. particle size=10-20micron, supplied by Graphite India, color=black, d.=1.75g/cm3, max. temp.=3600C, Young modulus=4.8GPa, elec. resistivity=7.5E(-5) ohm*cm and carbon-graphite%=30-70
Mixing / Blending method: PP ground to obtain finer particcles (212-250micron), added graphite powder, tumble mixed at ca. 400rpm for 4h using magnetic stirrer without heating

Reference: Julia, A King; Michael, D Via; Michelle, E King; Ibrahim, Miskioglu; Gregg, R Bogucki , Journal of Applied Polymer Science , 121 , 4 , 2273-2281 (2011)
Remarks: [PC] Lexan;HF1130-111;Sabic, MFR(300C, 1.2kg)=25g/10min, d.=1.2g/cc, electric resistivity=1E(17)ohm*cm, thermal cond.=0.19W/(m*K), [CNT] FIBRIL nanotube;Hyperion Catalysis International's, outside diam.=10nm, l=10micron, BET (N2) surface area=250m2/g, d.=2.0g/cc of nanotube wall and 1.75g/cc for the hollow nanotube
Mixing / Blending method: Pre-dried PC and CNT melt mixed at 290C and 250rpm using corotating intermeshing twin-screw extruder and pelletized
[elecon] condition: 23 [C] , 50%RH, bar-shaped sample conditioned for 2days before test

Name: poly(prop-1-ene)
Reference: Cheng, H; Pan, Y; Sahoo, N; Chong, K; Li, L; Chan, S; Zhao, J , Journal of Applied Polymer Science , 124 , 2 , 1117-1127 (2012)
Remarks: [polypropylene(PP)]average molecular weight 190000, purchased from Sigma-Aldrich, [multiwalled carbon nanotube(MWCNT)]Baytubes C 150 HP, purity>95%, diameter=5-20nm, length=1-10micron, number of wall=3-15, bulk density=140-230kg/m3, purchased from Bayer Material Science(Germany)
Mixing / Blending method: [blending]PP and MWCNT blended via twin-screw microcompounder at 180C and 30rpm for 15min
[proc] Injection: injection molded at 200C and 600bars for 10s using a mini-injection machine
